==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Favus
<hw>Fa"vus</hw> <pr>(f⟦amac⟧"v⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
honeycomb.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease of the
scalp, produced by a vegetable parasite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tile or flagstone cut into an hexagonal shape to
produce a honeycomb pattern, as in a pavement; -- called also
<altname>favas</altname> and <altname>sectila</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Mollett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fawe</ent>⟦br⟧
